      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, quick question - r tariffs actually a good way to protect local jobs, or do they just end up making things more expensive for regular people?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are often intended to protect local jobs by shielding domestic industries from foreign competition, but they frequently fail to achieve this goal in the long run. Instead, the costs are almost always passed down to consumers in the form of higher prices for goods and essential services. While some specific sectors may gain short-term advantages, the overall economic effect is a reduction in consumer purchasing power and potential job losses elsewhere in the supply chain.",
